00:00:02.440 --> 00:00:08.950
&gt;&gt;commentator: So, today we are excited to
welcome Jack Bowen to discuss his latest work,

00:00:08.950 --> 00:00:14.610
his third: "If You Can Read This: The Philosophy
of Bumper Stickers."

00:00:14.610 --> 00:00:20.670
By way of introduction, Jack graduated from
Stanford University in 1995 with honors in

00:00:20.670 --> 00:00:26.750
human biology. While he was there he was also
an All-American water polo player. He went

00:00:26.750 --> 00:00:34.160
on to earn his Master's Degree in philosophy
at Cal State. Currently, Jack teaches philosophy

00:00:34.160 --> 00:00:37.460
and coaches water polo at Menlo School in
Atherton.

00:00:37.460 --> 00:00:43.809
His debut novel, "The Dream Weaver" made the
San Francisco Chronicle best seller list for

00:00:43.809 --> 00:00:49.949
March 2006 and was one of Kepler Book Stores
top ten sellers for that year.

00:00:49.949 --> 00:00:57.239
His second work, "Journey Through the Landscape
of Philosophy" is a college philosophy textbook.

00:00:57.239 --> 00:01:03.429
And he's accom, accompanied both of these
by publishing in numerous philosophy journals

00:01:03.429 --> 00:01:04.909
primarily in ethics.

00:01:04.909 --> 00:01:10.440
And finally, Jack is a senior lecturer with
the Great Books Program at Stanford University

00:01:10.440 --> 00:01:11.750
in the summers.

00:01:11.750 --> 00:01:17.780
He's an avid musician, member of numerous
bands. He currently lives in Redwood City

00:01:17.780 --> 00:01:22.820
with his wife and their dog Chewbacca and
two cats, Patches and Plato. [laughs]

00:01:22.820 --> 00:01:25.240
So please join me in welcoming Jack Bowen.

00:01:25.240 --> 00:01:26.240
[applause]

